Uses of Package

  • Classes in Unnamed Package used by Unnamed Package
    Class
    Description
    Branch
    The Branch class represents a branch of a restaurant or business.
    BranchApp
    The BranchApp class manages a list of Branch objects and provides methods for saving and loading the branch data from a serialized file.
    Menu
    The Menu class represents a menu and manages a list of menu items.
    MenuItem
    The MenuItem class represents a single item in a menu.
    MenuItem.MenuCategory
     
    NonPermutableBranch
    The NonPermutableBranch interface represents a contractual obligation for classes that need to handle requests to process or manage different types of Branch objects.
    NonPermutableNull
    The NonPermutableNull interface defines a standard method for executing requests without requiring additional parameters.
    Order
    Represents an order in a shopping system, handling item management in a cart, order status updates, and dining options.
    OrderItem
    Represents an item within an order, extending MenuItem with additional features like quantity and customisation options.
    PaymentList
    The PaymentList class represents a payment item with an item ID and a payment type.
    PaymentList.PaymentType
    An enumeration representing the different types of payment methods.
    PaymentMethod
    The PaymentMethod interface defines a contract for payment methods.
    Permutable
    The Permutable abstract class extends the BranchApp class and provides an abstract method request() that must be implemented by concrete subclasses.
    PermutableBranch
    The PermutableBranch class is an abstract class that extends BranchApp and provides a method for requesting permutations of a branch.
    User
    The User class represents a user in the system.
    UserController
    The UserController interface defines methods for user authentication.
    UserView
    The UserView interface defines a method for displaying user-related information.
